Four Americans who were held hostage at a synagogue in Texas have been rescued thanks to the efforts of state, local, and federal law enforcement. The author expresses gratitude for the cooperative and fearless actions of law enforcement in rescuing the hostages. They also send love and strength to the congregation and the Jewish community affected by the incident. While the motivations of the hostage taker are still being investigated, the author affirms their commitment to standing against antisemitism and extremism in the country. The author concludes by praising the men and women of law enforcement for their proud and commendable work.